For this app to work your Citrix NetScaler data must be extracting fields correctly. The Field Extractions included in this app are configured for the NetScaler v 9.0 and higher. 

##### What's New #####
5.0
- Support for NetScaler version 10.x
- Dashboards converted to Simple XML
- Splunk CIM Compliance
- Requires separate IPFIX collector http://apps.splunk.com/app/1801/


###### Package Contents ######

The Splunk for Citrix NetScaler package includes:
* Splunk_TA_Citrix-NetScaler: Provides field extractions and collection mechanisms for NetScaler syslog and AppFlow data.
* SplunkforCitrixNetScaler: Provides dashboards and saved searches


###### Upgrading from versions prior to 5.0.x ######1. On your Splunk server, remove the following:
    * $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/Splunk_TA_NSIndexer
    * $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/Splunk_TA_IPFIX_UDP_NIX (if applicable)
    * $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/Splunk_TA_IPFIX_UDP_WIN (if applicable)
2. Follow the rest of the installation instructions below.
3. When uploading the installer file, make sure the "Upgrade app" is selected.

###### Installation ######

1. Install the separate IPFIX modular input (http://apps.splunk.com/app/1801/).  This input is required to collect AppFlow data.
2. Log into Splunk Web.
3. Click Apps > Manage Apps.
4. Click Install App from File.
5. Upload the SplunkforCitrixNetScaler-x.x.x.tar.gz installer file.
6. Restart Splunk.


## Installation Notes  ##
Once Splunk restarts, the Splunk_TA_Citrix-NetScaler folder should be copied to $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps.  If this does not happen, check $SPLUNK_HOME/var/log/splunk/netscaler_installer.log for issues.

Note:
$SPLUNK_HOME default directories:
- Windows = C:\Program Files\Splunk
- *nix    = /opt/splunk
- Mac     = /Applications/Splunk

## Manual TA Installation ##
The Splunk_TA_Citrix-NetScaler can also manually be copied from:
   $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/SplunkforCitrixNetScaler/appserver/addons
to:
   $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps



